                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17740112-63-off331 t17740112-63-cd334"></join> the prisoner came into my shop to buy a skain of silk, and a skain of mohairs: I came into the shop time enough to receive the money; my servant said he thought he had concealed some silk; he charged him with it, and searched him in my presence, and found the silk upon him: it was in the inside pocket. (The silk produced and deposed to).</p>
